# User Activity Report Generation

## Overview

This rule provides a systematic approach to generate concise, bullet-point reports of changes implemented by a specific user within a specific time period. The report analyzes git history to understand feature implementations, API integrations, form building, and overall project progress.

## When to Use

Use this rule when the user requests:

- Activity reports for specific developers
- Progress reports for time periods
- Feature implementation summaries
- Work summaries (e.g., "what did I do yesterday?", "what was done from Dec 30 to Jan 1?")
- Developer contribution analysis

## Report Format

### Short Report Structure

```markdown
# Activity Report: [Author Name] - [Date Range]

## Summary

- **Total Commits**: X commits
- **Files Changed**: X files
- **Lines Added**: +X
- **Lines Removed**: -X
- **Primary Focus**: [Main feature/area]

## Features Implemented

### [Feature Name]

- **Building form of [feature]**: Description of form implementation
  - Files: `path/to/form.tsx`, `path/to/form-options.ts`
  - Status: Completed/In Progress

### [Another Feature]

- **Integrating [API/Service] API**: Description of API integration
  - Files: `query/[feature]/[feature]-query.ts`, `lib/api/[service].ts`
  - Endpoints: `/api/endpoint`, `/api/another-endpoint`
  - Status: Completed/In Progress

## Bug Fixes

- **Fixed [issue]**: Brief description
  - Files: `path/to/fix.tsx`
  - Impact: High/Medium/Low

## Improvements & Refactoring

- **Refactored [component/module]**: Description
  - Files: `path/to/refactored.tsx`
  - Benefits: Performance, maintainability, etc.

## Project Progress

- **Feature X**: [Progress percentage or status]
- **Feature Y**: [Progress percentage or status]
- **Overall**: [Summary of project state]
```

## Analysis Workflow

### Step 1: Gather Git History

#### Filter by Author and Date Range

**Author Name Matching:**

- Git author names can be case-sensitive or case-insensitive depending on git config
- Use flexible matching: try exact match first, then case-insensitive
- Common formats: "First Last", "first last", "FirstLast"

**Date Range Formats:**

- **Relative dates**: "yesterday", "last week", "last month"
- **Absolute dates**: "2024-12-30", "Dec 30 2024", "30 Dec 2024"
- **Date ranges**: "2024-12-30 to 2025-01-01", "Dec 30 to Jan 1", "30 Dec to 1 Jan"

**Git Commands:**

```bash
# Get commits by author and date range (relative)
git log --author="Salah Mohsen" --since="yesterday" --until="now" --oneline

# Get commits by author and date range (absolute)
git log --author="Salah Mohsen" --since="2024-12-30" --until="2025-01-01" --oneline

# Get commits with full details
git log --author="Salah Mohsen" --since="2024-12-30" --until="2025-01-01" \
  --pretty=format:"%h - %an, %ar : %s" --name-status

# Get statistics
git log --author="Salah Mohsen" --since="2024-12-30" --until="2025-01-01" \
  --stat --oneline

# Get file changes summary
git log --author="Salah Mohsen" --since="2024-12-30" --until="2025-01-01" \
  --pretty=format:"" --name-only | sort | uniq -c | sort -rn

# Get diff statistics
git log --author="Salah Mohsen" --since="2024-12-30" --until="2025-01-01" \
  --numstat --pretty=format:"%h %s"
```

#### Handle Date Range Variations

```bash
# Parse user input for date ranges
# Examples:
# - "yesterday" → --since="yesterday" --until="now"
# - "30 Dec to 1 Jan" → --since="2024-12-30" --until="2025-01-01"
# - "Dec 30 to Jan 1" → --since="2024-12-30" --until="2025-01-01"
# - "from 30 Dec to 1 Jan" → --since="2024-12-30" --until="2025-01-01"

# For current year, assume current year if not specified
# For year transitions, handle appropriately (Dec 30 to Jan 1 = Dec 30 of current year to Jan 1 of next year)
```

### Step 2: Analyze Commits and Changes

#### Categorize Changes

**Feature Implementation Detection:**

Look for patterns indicating new features:

```bash
# New form components
git log --author="Salah Mohsen" --since="..." --until="..." \
  --name-only --pretty=format:"" | grep -E "(form|Form)" | grep -E "\.tsx?$"

# New API integrations
git log --author="Salah Mohsen" --since="..." --until="..." \
  --name-only --pretty=format:"" | grep -E "(query|api|fetcher)" | grep -E "\.ts$"

# New pages/routes
git log --author="Salah Mohsen" --since="..." --until="..." \
  --name-only --pretty=format:"" | grep -E "app/.*/page\.tsx$"

# New components
git log --author="Salah Mohsen" --since="..." --until="..." \
  --name-only --pretty=format:"" | grep -E "components/.*\.tsx$"
```

**API Integration Detection:**

```bash
# Check for new endpoints
git log --author="Salah Mohsen" --since="..." --until="..." \
  --all -- "query-client/endpoints.ts" | grep -E "^\+.*ENDPOINTS"

# Check for new query files
git log --author="Salah Mohsen" --since="..." --until="..." \
  --name-only --pretty=format:"" | grep -E "query/.*-query\.ts$"

# Check for new mutations
git log --author="Salah Mohsen" --since="..." --until="..." \
  --name-only --pretty=format:"" | grep -E "query/.*-mutations\.ts$"
```

**Form Building Detection:**

```bash
# Check for form files
git log --author="Salah Mohsen" --since="..." --until="..." \
  --name-only --pretty=format:"" | grep -E "(form|Form)" | grep -E "\.tsx?$"

# Check for form options/schemas
git log --author="Salah Mohsen" --since="..." --until="..." \
  --name-only --pretty=format:"" | grep -E "form-options" | grep -E "\.ts$"
```

### Step 3: Deep Analysis of Changes

#### Analyze File Changes

For each significant change, determine:

1. **What was implemented?**
   - New feature (form, table, page, API integration)
   - Bug fix
   - Refactoring
   - Improvement

2. **How was it implemented?**
   - Files created/modified
   - Dependencies added
   - Patterns followed

3. **What's the purpose?**
   - User-facing feature
   - Internal improvement
   - API integration
   - Bug resolution

#### Extract Specific Implementation Details

**Form Implementations:**

```bash
# Get form-related changes
git log --author="Salah Mohsen" --since="..." --until="..." \
  --all -- "**/forms/**" "**/form-options/**" --pretty=format:"%s" --name-only

# Analyze form files to extract:
# - Form name/feature
# - Fields implemented
# - Validation rules
# - Integration points
```

**API Integrations:**

```bash
# Get API-related changes
git log --author="Salah Mohsen" --since="..." --until="..." \
  --all -- "query/**" "query-client/**" --pretty=format:"%s" --name-only

# Analyze to extract:
# - API service name (e.g., "Space API", "Payment API")
# - Endpoints added
# - Query/mutation implementations
# - Integration points
```

**Feature Building:**

```bash
# Get feature-related changes
git log --author="Salah Mohsen" --since="..." --until="..." \
  --all -- "app/**" "components/**" --pretty=format:"%s" --name-only

# Analyze to extract:
# - Feature name
# - Components created
# - Pages created
# - Complete feature scope
```

### Step 4: Understand Project Progress

#### Before/After Analysis

**Get State Before Date Range:**

```bash
# Get commits before the start date to understand starting point
git log --author="Salah Mohsen" --until="2024-12-30" --oneline | head -10

# Get file structure before changes
git show $(git rev-list -1 --before="2024-12-30" --author="Salah Mohsen" HEAD):path/to/file 2>/dev/null || echo "File didn't exist"
```

**Get State After Date Range:**

```bash
# Get commits after the end date to see continuation
git log --author="Salah Mohsen" --since="2025-01-01" --oneline | head -10

# Get current file structure
git show HEAD:path/to/file
```

**Compare States:**

```bash
# Compare feature completeness
git diff $(git rev-list -1 --before="2024-12-30" HEAD) HEAD -- "app/(app)/feature/**"

# Compare query implementations
git diff $(git rev-list -1 --before="2024-12-30" HEAD) HEAD -- "query/feature/**"
```

#### Progress Indicators

**Feature Completion Status:**

- **New Feature Started**: Files created, basic structure in place
- **In Progress**: Core functionality implemented, some parts missing
- **Completed**: All components, forms, queries, pages implemented
- **Enhanced**: Additional improvements to existing feature

**API Integration Status:**

- **Initial Integration**: Endpoints added, basic queries created
- **Complete Integration**: Queries, mutations, error handling, types all implemented
- **Enhanced**: Additional endpoints, optimizations, error handling improvements

**Form Implementation Status:**

- **Form Created**: Basic form structure
- **Fields Added**: All form fields implemented
- **Validation Added**: Schema and validation rules implemented
- **Complete**: Form, validation, submission, error handling all done

